            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1438758673,
            "creation_date": 1438758673,
            "body": "<p><code>onBackPressureLatest<\/code> is your friend here. :)\n<a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/rx/Observable.html#onBackpressureLatest()\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/rx/Observable.html#onBackpressureLatest()<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 31825729,
            "question_id": 31815989
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/51a3a4349309b3ba7a448fa600503807?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 216605,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 471955,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/471955/dave-moten",
                "reputation": 12137,
                "display_name": "Dave Moten",
                "accept_rate": 0
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1438729978,
            "creation_date": 1438729978,
            "body": "<p><code>Observable.debounce<\/code> sounds like what you need. In the example below the latest emission only from observable in each 200ms window will be sent to the observer.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>observable\n    .debounce(200, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)\n    .subscribe(observer);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 31820898,
            "question_id": 31815989
        }
    ],
